<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: overflow hidden establishes a new block formatting context</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Louis14 Project" href="https://github.com/nicbarker/nicbarker.github.io" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visufx.html#overflow" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#block-formatting" />
  <link rel="match" href="overflow-hidden-bfc-001-ref.xht" />
  <meta name="assert" content="An element with overflow other than visible establishes a new block formatting context. This means it should contain floated children and not collapse margins with them." />

  <style type="text/css">
  .container {
    width: 100px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background-color: green;
  }

  .float {
    float: left;
    width: 100px;
    height: 100px;
    background-color: green;
  }
  </style>
 </head>
 <body>

  <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="float"></div>
  </div>

 </body>
</html>
